Introduction

YOUNG POSSE is a South Korean girl group formed by DSP Media and BEATS Entertainment. On June 22, 2023, DSP Media announced the debut of a new five-member girl group in collaboration with Beats Entertainment. This marks their first girl group since their debut of APRIL in 2015. The group's name, Young Posse, was revealed on July 12.

The group name comes from the Latin word "posse", meaning "can do" or "possible". YOUNG POSSE stands for "a group of young people gathered with a purpose" showing how we can achieve whatever we want by joining forces rather than being alone.

On July 16, 2023, Young Posse made their first public appearance at the RBW label concert, DSP's parent company. Later, on September 19, a teaser video for their debut was released. They made their official debut on October 18, 2023, with the mini album "MACARONI CHEESE EP".

On September 9, 2024, Young Posse won the "Hot Potential Award" at The Fact Music Awards, a 2-day event (September 8-9) held at Kyocera Dome in Osaka, Japan.
